## Original checkout integrity

The original checkout remained at `084b3b9ee6a1434e38a5bf23eee8266c43b3522d` throughout. `git status --short` was clean at start, after `git fetch origin`, and at the end. A transient untracked `.claude/settings.local.json.tmp.*` harness artifact appeared momentarily and disappeared on the next check; it was not tracked repository content.

## Disposable test environment

A disposable clone was checked out at `b348df52956f647216927599bae5637647e73f39`, confirmed as the then-current `origin/main`, and clean before the test.

Files inspected:

- `system/nexus_lab/snapshot.py`
- `system/nexus_lab/audit_integrity.py`
- `tests/test_audit_git_tree_binding.py`
- `operations/audits/AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND/results/codex-documentary-review/R005_FIDELITY_REVIEW.evidence`

## Baseline checks

| Command | Result |
|---|---|
| `./nexus doctor` | PASS, exit 0 |
| `python3 -m unittest discover -s tests -v` | 37/37 PASS, exit 0 |
| `./nexus verify` | PASS, exit 0 |
| `./nexus audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND` | PASS before attack, exit 0 |

## Independent stronger replacement test

The reviewer independently modified the real R002 target snapshot in the disposable clone by replacing `AGENTS.md` payload bytes, then regenerated:

- `_nexus/PAYLOAD_MANIFEST.sha256`;
- `_nexus/PACKAGE_MANIFEST.sha256`;
- `_nexus/SNAPSHOT_METADATA.json`;
- `TARGET.json.target_archive_sha256`;
- target archive sidecar;
- loose `MANIFEST.sha256`;
- audit pack and its sidecar.

The first attempt reproduced the same self-referential `MANIFEST.sha256` harness bug identified during R005. The disposable clone was reverted and the harness corrected by excluding `MANIFEST.sha256` and the audit-pack sidecar from the rebuild walk.

The corrected replacement then passed all internal consistency checks:

- `verify_snapshot()` returned PASS;
- `verify_manifest_pack()` returned PASS;
- loose and packed `MANIFEST.sha256` were byte-identical.

The complete replacement was committed only inside the disposable clone as commit `a860ad2`; `git status --short` was clean afterward.

## Decisive result

Running:

```text
./nexus audit-check --audit-id AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND
```

returned exit 2 with:

```text
NEXUS ERROR: Snapshot payload manifest does not match the immutable Git tree at target_commit.
```

The replacement was valid, internally self-consistent, and committed with a clean Git worktree. The decisive rejection was therefore the R006 `verify_snapshot_against_git_tree` binding, not a digest, manifest, pack-validity, or dirty-worktree check.

## Verdict

`AUDOBS_0003_REMEDIATION_CONFIRMED`

R006 closes the broader condition identified by the Codex documentary review: a coherently committed replacement of the snapshot and all adjacent audit declarations is rejected when its payload does not equal the immutable Git tree at `target_commit`.

## Limitations

- The pass did not inspect the R005 retest report or the full preserved original Claude evidence set.
- The critical-path Git-status branch was not separately attacked in this pass; the payload-to-Git-tree branch was isolated and exercised.
- The test covered the declared target commit with altered payload, not substitution of a different declared commit tree.
- No real branch, tag, target, snapshot, ledger, or remote state was modified or pushed.
